    <item>
      <title>Value and Uses of New DoD AAs</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magiciantactics&amp;message.id=413#M413</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#9933cc&gt;Well, looking at the new AA list (but not having tried any of these yet), these seem to me&amp;nbsp;to be the most useful AAs for us in DOD:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Darkvision(9):&amp;nbsp; Permanent See Invis (hassle factor reduced, one less buff/aug/effect needed)&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Silent Casting(25):&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Reduces aggro (if the wizzies are afk, we won't get aggro anyway...hehe)&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Elemental Ferocity(18):&amp;nbsp; Our pet flurries more (I'm assuming the flurrying does something of course...)&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Guardian of Fire(18): Our Servant of Ro does more damage (how much more? I assume he is doing damage in the first place, of course...since the filters don't show any...)&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;My doubts:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Avoidance AAs--will these keep us from being one-rounded?&amp;nbsp; Do they now?&amp;nbsp; Will they later?&amp;nbsp; I haven't invested much here given my existing doubts about whether they help non melees anyway.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Mitigation AAs--will these do anything for us since our AC probably won't rise to the level at which they do something?&amp;nbsp; I read somewhere&amp;nbsp;that if your AC isn't high enough, these don't do much (melee boards, and they would know). Has anyone tested these, even the ones we have now?&amp;nbsp; Don't have these--see the doubts above.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;My jealousies:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I admit it at least!&amp;nbsp; I'm not usually a jealous person but, I have my moments--luckily I also somewhat play these classes (enchanter and wizzy).&amp;nbsp; I say "somewhat" because magician is definitely my main.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff33cc&gt;Wizzy:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Silent Casting:&amp;nbsp; They do more damage, get more aggro, and thus get more value from these...small jealousy here.&amp;nbsp; Probably still more a dps jealousy.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hastened Mind Crash:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The new and effective concussion--jealousy issue?&amp;nbsp; See above...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Pyromancy:&amp;nbsp; Causes possible debuffing to fire with nukes.&amp;nbsp; Jealousy issue--they get a debuff for their highest dps nuke...will it&amp;nbsp;land&amp;nbsp;better than mine?&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Translocational Anchor:&amp;nbsp; Prevents a mob from gating.&amp;nbsp; Jealousy--wow what a useful AA!!!&amp;nbsp; This saves the whole group on a gater.&amp;nbsp; I have nothing that is useful to others like this in my inventory.&amp;nbsp; Can it be resisted?&amp;nbsp; Huge potential raid utility perhaps?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Mastery of Fury:&amp;nbsp; Increases critting chance...jealousy--I didn't get any increase of this kind, and wizzies were already way ahead of me in nuking crits.&amp;nbsp; It seems like.&amp;nbsp; Its passive unlike the hotkey AA stuff I get to increase damage, right?&amp;nbsp; Hmmm....&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;Enchanter:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Edict of Command:&amp;nbsp; A charm that sticks for a set duration--wow nice new cc method (I assume the dps has been nerfed of course).&amp;nbsp; I have nothing that can save a group like this...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Deep Sleep:&amp;nbsp; A mez has a chance to strongly disable the mob after mez wears off.&amp;nbsp; Nice--huge increase in group survivability.&amp;nbsp; Is it a good chance or it only works one time out of 1000?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Actually, I 'm only marginally jealous of enchanters, with their huge resists to mez.&amp;nbsp; They end up tanking if there is no off tank, and their tanking is about like mine, even with runes.&amp;nbsp; Actually, its a lot worse than mine,&amp;nbsp;when I consider&amp;nbsp;my pet, who is better than their runes at offtanking (lol!).&amp;nbsp; They over-nerfed enchanters :(&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So I'm happy to see that they get an AA to give them a better self rune (25 AAs--hopefully its A LOT of hp....).&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Of course, enchanters will continue to be most useful in a tough melee heavy group (survival is key), where someone can non-damage off tank for mezzing (since mez needs a pretash now).&amp;nbsp; So there will only be token nukers (6 spots:&amp;nbsp; Healer, tank, offtank, slower/chanter/shaman, puller/dps, dps) unless you replace the chanter with monk/shaman/bst combo of some sort.&amp;nbsp; In which case, no nuker because no mana buffers.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Question: assuming they do still want a mana dependant dps'er, why get a mage for that spot when you can get a wizzy (high dps) or druid (backup healer and dps)?&amp;nbsp; Hmmmm...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;We'll still do fine on the less-tough mobs and areas as mages.&amp;nbsp; I'll see whether those other AA abilities in wizzy and enchanter really work well.&amp;nbsp; Who knows--maybe they'll be like mana burn?&amp;nbsp; I hope not, as it would be nice to keep some casters in the "highly desired" spot for groups.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I admit it--I am irritated that there are no really, really cool sounding mage AAs coming, that I can see, unless I'm missing something--thats why I'm posting, in case someone can point out what I missed.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;PS to Developers:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;When you see the numbers playing at high levels&amp;nbsp;in a class dropping, its because you haven't balanced them well in the game, even if you have in your tests and on paper.&amp;nbsp; They should be ramped up in power (or UTILITY) at that level of the game--you can nerf later on in another expansion.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; You will have to noticeably&amp;nbsp;&lt;EM&gt;overpower &lt;/EM&gt;them due to the widespread perception that they aren't as valuable, as shown by the lower numbers playing that class at that level.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Also, anything the parsers don't show, doesn't exist in the minds of players...FYI :) :) :)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#000000&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;Haha, no offense I hope.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
