      <title>Anti Pet Raid Bias</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=magiciantactics&amp;message.id=374#M374</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;We mages need something to be done about the anti-pet bias on raids.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;In order to accommodate pet classes, old school raiders&amp;nbsp; have&amp;nbsp;to incorporate methods of dealing with&amp;nbsp;pet push into their strategy and directives to the raid; they also have to deal with the much higher risk if an inexperienced,&amp;nbsp;incompetent, or&amp;nbsp;AA-poor&amp;nbsp;player doesn't adequately control their pet.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;They don't want to.&amp;nbsp; They don't think the benefit is worth including the pet in their raid, and view including pets as a concession to pet owners, as opposed to being glad the pet is there and doing its thing.&amp;nbsp; They don't believe pets are worth it, and are just pacifying pet classes unless someone doesn't control their pet, in which case they get rid of all pets.&amp;nbsp; Because why not?&amp;nbsp; They aren't that much more dps.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;This is true even though pet classes can indeed finally control their pets on raids (after years of not being able to), barring push which we cannot adequately control, especially its cumulative effect with lots of pets with flurrying AAs, etc.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;So we need pets to be grossly overpowered.&amp;nbsp; Yes, make them so overpowered people scream for a nerf.&amp;nbsp; Leave it that way till raiders figure out how to use pets, give collective pet commands, deal wtih pet push, and respect pet classes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;Then reset pets to what they should be.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;I can dream can't I?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
